{
  "texts": [
    "All hosting services must establish user-friendly and accessible mechanisms to allow any individual or entity to submit a notice identifying and explaining the illegality of content (Recital 52).",
    "Notices can also be sent by certified \"trusted flaggers\" with expertise in identifying illegal material (Article 15, Recital 61, 62), EU member state authorities, and European Commission bodies.",
    "Hosting services are also required to inform law enforcement authorities when they become aware of suspected serious criminal offenses (Article 18).Upon receiving a notice, hosting services must expeditiously assess content's legality, remove or disable access to verified illegal material, and inform the notifier.",
    "Exact timeframes are specified based on notice source.",
    "For notices by individuals, hosting services must provide feedback about action taken without undue delay, and normally within 7 days."
  ]
}